-- Italy's Barilla tests Chinese tastes for wok pasta
-- By Francesca Landini
-- Fri Dec 05, 2014 11:23AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Dec 5 (Reuters) - Barilla, the world's biggest pasta maker, is testing Chinese appetites for quick pasta meals that can be made in a wok which went on sale in the southern region of Guangzhou.

"We had a very positive response from Chinese retailers," said a spokesman for Barilla on Friday, adding the group had  put the product - Pasta Pronto - on the shelves of more than 1,000 supermarkets and 750 convenience stores.The new product, which was launched officially on Nov. 25, is the outcome of more than two years of research to create a pasta meal in a wok, without using pots and drainers.